olive oil
2 clove garlic
½ bunch baby broccoli
1 packet green beans
1 carrot
2 potato
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Prosciutto
1 packet Lamb Shortloin
1 packet Flaked Almonds
1 packet Hollandaise

• See ‘Top Roast Tips!’ (below left).
• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic.
• Trim baby broccoli and green beans.
• Slice carrot into sticks.
• Place carrots on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with
olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Roast
until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• While the carrots are roasting, bring a medium
saucepan of salted water to the boil.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water until easily
pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
• Drain and return to the pan. Add the butter,
milk, grated Parmesan cheese and a generous
pinch of salt, then mash until smooth. Cover to
keep warm.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the
potato unpeeled!

• While the potato is cooking, lay 2-3 slices of
prosciutto, slightly overlapping on their long
sides on a second lined oven tray.
• Place one piece of lamb shortloin across
the prosciutto. Wrap prosciutto around
lamb and place seam-side down on the oven
tray. Repeat with the remaining lamb
and prosciutto.
• When the carrots have 10 minutes cook time
remaining, roast lamb in the oven for
7-10 minutes for medium or until cooked to
your liking.
• Transfer to a plate to rest.

• While the lamb is roasting, heat a large frying
pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of
olive oil.
• Cook baby broccoli and green beans, tossing,
until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and flaked almonds and cook,
stirring until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to
serving plates.

TIP: Add a dash of water to the pan to help speed up
the veggie cooking process.

• Return frying pan to medium heat, then add
hollandaise and a splash of water and cook
until fragrant and thickened slightly, 1 minute.

• Slice prosciutto-wrapped lamb.
• Divide cheesy mash between the plates with
garlicky veggies.
• Top with lamb.
• Spoon over hollandaise to serve. Enjoy!